Text.SourceString: You can understand my language? Impressive. How come?
Text.LocalizedString: You can understand my language? Impressive. How come?

Text.SourceString: I understand you. Am I smart?!
Text.LocalizedString: I understand you. Am I smart?!

Text.SourceString: Greetings, $player. What can I help you with today?
Text.LocalizedString: Greetings, $player. What can I help you with today?

Text.SourceString: Olan and I cook huge meals for festivals and holidays. They take all day, literally a whole day!
Text.LocalizedString: Olan and I cook huge meals for festivals and holidays. They take all day, literally a whole day!

Text.SourceString: Do you people do things like that, too?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you people do things like that, too?

Text.SourceString: You look hungry, $player.
Text.LocalizedString: You look hungry, $player.

Text.SourceString: Just grab whatever you want. I don't think <NPCName>Olan</> cares.
Text.LocalizedString: Just grab whatever you want. I don't think <NPCName>Olan</> cares.

Text.SourceString: We're making plain meals today for the family. Rumor has it the King has a tummy problem, but you didn't hear it from me.
Text.LocalizedString: We're making plain meals today for the family. Rumor has it the King has a tummy problem, but you didn't hear it from me.

Text.SourceString: I need a sugar boost, $player. Got anything sweet on you?
Text.LocalizedString: I need a sugar boost, $player. Got anything sweet on you?

Text.SourceString: Don’t tell my boss, but sometimes I get tired of cooking. I don’t know how he’s done nothing but cook for a bazillion tides.
Text.LocalizedString: Don’t tell my boss, but sometimes I get tired of cooking. I don’t know how he’s done nothing but cook for a bazillion tides.

Text.SourceString: I could never get tired of eating, though!
Text.LocalizedString: I could never get tired of eating, though!

Text.SourceString: We’ve got a busy day ahead of us. The only thing we can do about it is put on our aprons and get to work.
Text.LocalizedString: We’ve got a busy day ahead of us. The only thing we can do about it is put on our aprons and get to work.

Text.SourceString: There are so many different foods here. Apparently, the king will eat just about anything.//<portrait=concerned>The Queen is a little picky, though.
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many different foods here. Apparently, the king will eat just about anything.//<portrait=concerned>The Queen is a little picky, though.

Text.SourceString: What should I have for dinner tomorrow?
Text.LocalizedString: What should I have for dinner tomorrow?

Text.SourceString: I heard you're some sort of royalty on land. Do you also have a team of cooks?
Text.LocalizedString: I heard you're some sort of royalty on land. Do you also have a team of cooks?

Text.SourceString: We use a lot of labu here, along with kelp. The Queen even harvests them herself sometimes.
Text.LocalizedString: We use a lot of labu here, along with kelp. The Queen even harvests them herself sometimes.

Text.SourceString: Finally! A day off from standing in front of the stove.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally! A day off from standing in front of the stove.

Text.SourceString: The water feels deliciously cold today, too. Aaaahhhhh.
Text.LocalizedString: The water feels deliciously cold today, too. Aaaahhhhh.

Text.SourceString: Another tide, another meal for the royal family. What will it be today?
Text.LocalizedString: Another tide, another meal for the royal family. What will it be today?

Text.SourceString: I’m already looking forward to the cake I’m going to bake myself tonight. It’s gonna be so good!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m already looking forward to the cake I’m going to bake myself tonight. It’s gonna be so good!

Text.SourceString: I like having your company in the kitchen, but I’ve got to keep working or <NPCName>Olan</> will get mad at me.
Text.LocalizedString: I like having your company in the kitchen, but I’ve got to keep working or <NPCName>Olan</> will get mad at me.

Text.SourceString: He might even fire me. I don’t want that to happen. Adults don’t get fired from things.
Text.LocalizedString: He might even fire me. I don’t want that to happen. Adults don’t get fired from things.

Text.SourceString: That shrimp... It's quite a character, always zipping around the kitchen like it owns the place.//<portrait=annoyed>Kinda annoying sometimes, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: That shrimp... It's quite a character, always zipping around the kitchen like it owns the place.//<portrait=annoyed>Kinda annoying sometimes, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: Just yesterday, that shrimp managed to knock over a whole jar of sea salt. Can you believe it?
Text.LocalizedString: Just yesterday, that shrimp managed to knock over a whole jar of sea salt. Can you believe it?

Text.SourceString: One time, the shrimp almost got cooked! Jumped right into a pot of boiling water. Good thing <NPCName>Olan</>'s quick on his fins.
Text.LocalizedString: One time, the shrimp almost got cooked! Jumped right into a pot of boiling water. Good thing <NPCName>Olan</>'s quick on his fins.

Text.SourceString: I'm not his biggest fan, but he's kinda cute, you know. I don't want him hurt.
Text.LocalizedString: I'm not his biggest fan, but he's kinda cute, you know. I don't want him hurt.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes my friends and I play coral chase on the weekends. It’s where everyone hides and one person tries to find everyone inside the coral fields.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes my friends and I play coral chase on the weekends. It’s where everyone hides and one person tries to find everyone inside the coral fields.

Text.SourceString: It’s a lot of fun! And it’s a really good workout.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s a lot of fun! And it’s a really good workout.

Text.SourceString: What’s your favorite food of all time? Like, out of everything?
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your favorite food of all time? Like, out of everything?

Text.SourceString: I know, I know, it’s so hard to choose. I don’t think I could pick just one!
Text.LocalizedString: I know, I know, it’s so hard to choose. I don’t think I could pick just one!

Text.SourceString: Watch out! Hot cauldron coming through!
Text.LocalizedString: Watch out! Hot cauldron coming through!

Text.SourceString: I wonder what I’d be doing if I wasn’t <NPCName>Olan</>’s apprentice. Probably travelling or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I wonder what I’d be doing if I wasn’t <NPCName>Olan</>’s apprentice. Probably travelling or something.

Text.SourceString: I guess I have to contribute to merfolk society somehow.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess I have to contribute to merfolk society somehow.

Text.SourceString: You’re a farmer, right? Have you tried growing anything in that little plot of land by the gate?
Text.LocalizedString: You’re a farmer, right? Have you tried growing anything in that little plot of land by the gate?

Text.SourceString: I bet you could grow some really fresh ingredients there.
Text.LocalizedString: I bet you could grow some really fresh ingredients there.

Text.SourceString: Olan always seems like he’s got everything figured out. I hope I can be like that one day.
Text.LocalizedString: Olan always seems like he’s got everything figured out. I hope I can be like that one day.

Text.SourceString: I’m not always good at figuring things out.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not always good at figuring things out.

Text.SourceString: Olan has a very good reputation around here. Everyone knows he’s the best cook in the entire kingdom.
Text.LocalizedString: Olan has a very good reputation around here. Everyone knows he’s the best cook in the entire kingdom.

Text.SourceString: That’s why the king hired him!
Text.LocalizedString: That’s why the king hired him!

Text.SourceString: I know the palace better than just about anyone. Like, did you know there’s a hidden—
Text.LocalizedString: I know the palace better than just about anyone. Like, did you know there’s a hidden—

Text.SourceString: Oops! I probably shouldn’t have said that.
Text.LocalizedString: Oops! I probably shouldn’t have said that.

Text.SourceString: Working in a castle basically makes me royalty, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Working in a castle basically makes me royalty, right?

Text.SourceString: What a beautiful day for eating! Don’t you agree?
Text.LocalizedString: What a beautiful day for eating! Don’t you agree?

Text.SourceString: Every day’s a beautiful day for eating, really.
Text.LocalizedString: Every day’s a beautiful day for eating, really.

Text.SourceString: I don’t think I’d want to be a king. That seems like a lot of responsibility for one person.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t think I’d want to be a king. That seems like a lot of responsibility for one person.

Text.SourceString: I’ve got enough on my plate right now.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve got enough on my plate right now.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes after storms, you can see huge clouds of fish caught up in the currents.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes after storms, you can see huge clouds of fish caught up in the currents.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, though, you end up with trash. Now that's not fun at all.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, though, you end up with trash. Now that's not fun at all.
